this Source fork with BBCodeizer(MIT)

easy to use & care Performance

Only

BBCoder.enbbcode(string)
BBCoder.debbcode(string)

It's all

maybe you like use this:

[model(save/update)]
def before_save
  self.body = BBCoder.decode(ERB::Util.html_escape(self.body)) if self.body_changed?
end

[controller(update edit)]
def edit
  @post.body = BBCoder.encode(@post.body) # for WYSIWYG
end

so , when display will not take any process to de/encode BBCode again :)

& also support Helper

[view]

<%= bbcoder_encode(string) %>
<%= bbcoder_decode(string) %>

& if you using TinyMCE BBCode plugin , you can use %LIB_DIR%/support/TinyMCE/BBCode
to change original plugin